South African Equity Market: 1Time Holdings, JD Group, Morvest

-- B y   S i k o n a t h i   M a n t s h a n t s h a
-- 
2011-03-18T16:25:33Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-18/south-african-equity-market-1time-holdings-morvest-sasol-move.html
  South Africa ’s FTSE/JSE Africa All
Share Index snapped two days gains, losing 41.47, or 0.1
percent, to 30,748.44 at the 5 p.m. close in Johannesburg. The
measure has lost 1.6 percent this week. The following were among
the most active stocks in the South African market today.    1Time Holdings Ltd. (1TM)  (1TM SJ), the low-cost airline and
technical maintenance company, snapped three days of losses,
rising 3 cents, or 4.5 percent, to 70 cents. The company said it
will start operations from Johannesburg’s Lanseria Airport and
expand flights into other routes in the southern Africa region.  JD Group Ltd. (JDG SJ), a South African furniture retailer,
had its biggest one-day surge since May 12, rising 1.61 rand, or
3.7 percent, to 45.68 rand. The Retailer Liaison Committee, an
industry group, said in an e-mailed statement today that
furniture and appliances sales jumped 22 percent in February,
compared with a year ago.  Morvest Business Group Ltd. (MOR SJ), a computer-services
company, declined 1 cent, or 5.3 percent, to 18 cents. The
company said it has agreed to buy 50 percent of R&S Consulting
for 60 million rand ($8.5 million).  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sikonathi Mantshantsha in Johannesburg at 
